<item>
            <title>[LU-17647] lfs mirror extend: add --comp-flags-orig=FLAGS</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-17647</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The purpose of this new option&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
--comp-flags-orig=FLAGS&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;is to set flags on a file which the new mirror is originated from. Currently we can set the flags on the mirrored file, but sometimes we need symmetrically to set flag(s) on the original file. One example is Hot-pools, where files are created in fast pool have to set &apos;prefer&apos; flag immediately after mirroring them into cold pool. Currently this is done by spawning another lfs setstripe command. This process is suboptimal and also may be delayed.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="81448">LU-17647</key>
            <summary>lfs mirror extend: add --comp-flags-orig=FLAGS</summary>
                <type id="4" iconUrl="https://jira.whamcloud.com/secure/viewavatar?size=xsmall&amp;avatarId=11310&amp;avatarType=issuetype">Improvement</type>
