                                                                                <due></due>
                            <votes>0</votes>
                                    <watches>4</watches>
                                                                            <comments>
                            <comment id="407946" author="adilger" created="Sat, 16 Mar 2024 08:32:01 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I was thinking about this further, and I&apos;m not sure &quot;&lt;tt&gt;&amp;#45;&amp;#45;comp&amp;#45;flags&amp;#45;orig&lt;/tt&gt;&quot; will always be correct (even though I suggested this name originally.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If there are two original mirrors and a new one is being created, which component does the &quot;prefer&quot; go on?  I think another option would be:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;lfs mirror extend --comp-set [--mirror-id MIRROR_ID|--comp-id COMP_ID|--pool POOL] --comp-flags=FLAGS -N -E MIRROR_OPTIONS
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This allows selecting a mirror/component like &lt;tt&gt;lfs mirror split&lt;/tt&gt; and then setting &lt;tt&gt;FLAGS&lt;/tt&gt; on that component before starting the &quot;&lt;tt&gt;&amp;#45;N&lt;/tt&gt;&quot; mirror options.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
